	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-02-05T23:00:36">Bowleven plc is an independent exploration and development company focused on Africa. The Company has interests in Cameroon, Kenya and Zambia. In Cameroon, the Group operates the offshore shallow water Etinde Permit spread across 2,316 square kilometer (km2), where plans for a staged development of the liquids-rich discoveries on the acreage are advancing, and the onshore Bomono Permit spread in 2,328km2, where exploration drilling is planned. Its Cameroon operations are managed through EurOil Ltd, a wholly owned subsidiary of the Company. The Companys project in Kenya is in a hydrocarbon province block 11B, which is situated at the intersection of the tertiary and cretaceous East African Rift systems. Block 11B encompasses an area of 14,000km2 covering the Loeli, Lotikipi, Gatome and South Gatome basin.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-11-26T14:32:52">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 June 2015, BowLeven PLC revenues was not reported. Net loss increased from $13.5M to $89.9M. Higher net loss reflects Exchange rate loss increase of 37% to $2.4M (expense). Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items decreased from -$0.04 to -$0.28.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
